Goodbye, my dear Usbek, goodbye; you may be sure that I live only to adore you; my heart is full of you, and your absence, far from making me forget you, would inflame my passion, were it possible for it to become more violent.

The seraglio in Ispahan, the 12th of the Moon of Rebiab 1 1711|
